```js
fs.writeFile(localFileName, response.data, (fsError) =&gt; {
    if (fsError) {
        throw fsError;
    }
    // Send the file
    const url = &#39;&lt;yourApiUrl&gt;&#39;;
    const formData = new FormData();
    formData.append(&#39;file&#39;,fs.createReadStream(&#39;&lt;pathToFile&gt;&#39;), { knownLength: fs.statSync(&#39;&lt;pathToFile&gt;&#39;).size });
    const config = {
        headers: {
            ...formData.getHeaders(),
            &#39;Content-Length&#39;: formData.getLengthSync()
        }
    };
    axios.post(url, forData, { headers });
});
```

I&#39;m not super confident in the `// Send the file` section only because I can&#39;t test against your API. I got most of the code from [here](https://github.com/axios/axios/issues/789#issuecomment-508114703).

